at’s what it is.\n\n- William Golding, Lord of the Flies\n|\n. . . when it comes down to it, that’s what life is all about: showing up for the people you love, again and again, until you can’t show up anymore.\n\n- Rebecca Walker, Baby Love: Choosing Motherhood After a Lifetime of Ambivalence\n|\nIt is important that students bring a certain ragamuffin, barefoot irreverence to their studies; they are not here to worship what is known, but to question it.\n\n- Jacob Bronowski, The Ascent of Man\n|\nIn this world, it is too common for people to search for someone to lose themselves in. But I am already lost. I will look for someone to find myself in.\n\n- C.\n|\nIf there is any society where the leaders lack the knowledge and the importance of justice, then oppression will be a common neighbor of the citizens.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nHenry narrowed his eyes at me. 'You going somewhere?''Lacrosse field trip,' I said. 'I enjoy whacking the hell out of people with mallets.\n\n- Robin Benway, The Extraordinary Secrets of April, May, & June\n|\nDo not contemplate the Essence of the UnVeiled, for the UnVeiled therein your World does not hold to polarities, nor of your conjectures; Chapter 'The Unveiling\n\n- AainaA-Ridtz, The Sacred Key — Transcending Humanity\n|\nDear, I can't write, it's all a fantasy: a kind of circling obsession.\n\n- Philip Larkin, Philip Larkin: Letters to Monica\n|\nOf life's two chief prizes, beauty and truth, I found the first in a loving heart and the second in a laborer's hand.\n\n- Kahlil\n|\nInstead of falling, I am dancing with the wind.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dancing with the Wind: A True Story of Zen in the Art of Windsurfing\n|\nGod created you to be a great, special, and distinguished individual among others, for you to accomplish that which God has put in you\n\n- Sunday\n|\nTo reach your Destination, you need a Direction, but you can't get there without Inspiration!\n\n- RVM\n|\nI don't want truth, Palmer; I want smoke!' Captain Ahearn: Waiting For Willie Pete\n\n- Byron\n|\nYou are immortal till the very moment you die. Discover it, and stand untouchable.\n\n- VirusLord\n|\nNothing was true for long. In time, everything was deconstructed.\n\n- Sue Townsend, The Woman Who Went to Bed for a Year\n|\nStrive for perfection, knowing it will never be achieved.\n\n- Chris\n|\nThat was the day that I promised I'd never sing of love that does not exist. but darling, You are the only exception\n\n- Hayley\n|\nIf there is anything the devil will want to keep you from having, it is knowledge.\n\n- Sunday\n|\nBy studying yesterday, you will understand today.\n\n- Suzy Kassem, Rise Up and Salute the Sun: The Writings of Suzy Kassem\n|\nBecause the truth is, it isn't worth loving something if you aren't going to love it all the way.\n\n- Goldy Moldavsky, Kill the Boy Band\n|\nLife is power, don’t abuse it.\n\n- Israelmore Ayivor, Six Words Inspiration\n|\nYou can go your whole life collecting days, and none will outweigh the one you wish you had back.\n\n- Mitch Albom, For One More Day\n|\nGodliness must be presented with its profit and incentives, not only for the good of the nation and society, but of eternal value.\n\n- Sunday Adelaja, The Mountain of Ignorance\n|\nWith every challenge you face, there is an opportunity hidden that will lead you towards the path of wealth and abundance.\n\n- Stephen Richards, Be First: Achieve Every Dream\n|\nDo you always ask me the same questions you ask him?''It depends on whether or not I get an answer.\n\n- Anne Bishop, Daughter of the Blood\n|\nPsychology is a subject of life, death, and in-betweens.\n\n- Santosh\n|\nBooks are the shells of wisdom, which are split open for the pearls of character.\n\n- Bozorgmehr\n|\nThe essence of life does not consist in the lushness of your possessions, but in the richness of your heart.\n\n- Roy\n|\nThere comes that mysterious meeting in life when someone acknowledges who we are and what we can be, igniting the